## Summary Table

| Activation | Core Idea |
|---|---|
| Sigmoid | Compress to 0–1 |
| Tanh | Compress to -1–1, zero-centered |
| ReLU | Kill negatives, keep positives |
| Leaky ReLU | Almost kill negatives |
| ELU | Smoothly kill negatives |
| Swish | Self-gated, smooth ReLU |
| Softplus | Soft ReLU, never zero |
| Softmax | Turn scores into probabilities |

---

## Where to Start

**For MNIST:**
```
Hidden layers → ReLU
Output layer  → Softmax
```

Then swap the hidden activation and watch
how accuracy and training speed change.

